                        Angular - Front End Development


                            Basic Commands

            1. to create project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing


            2. to run a project - ng serve / ng serve --open


            3. to create component - ng g c component-name

            
            4. to create services - ng g s component-name

            
            5. to create directives - ng g d directive-name

            
            6. to build Angular application - ng build --prod





                        Basic Concepts

            1. component -to create {html,css,ts file} root component -Appcomponent

            2. Module - to add libraries to the project - root module - AppModule

            3. Data Binding - data sharing btw html and ts

                3.1 One way Binding

                    3.1.1 component to view
                        
                        3.1.1.1 String Interpolation: syntax - {{variable-name}}

                        3.1.1.2 Property Binding: 

                    3.1.2 View to Component

                        3.1.2.1 Event Binding- (event)="function-call()"

                        3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event- (event)="function-call()"

                        3.1.2.3 Template referencing variable - 

                3.2 Two Way Binding-

                        3.2.1 Using ngModeli- Import formmodule in AppModule 
                            syntax: [(ngModel)]="variable-name"
            
            4. Set a path for a component : defined in App Routing Module
                syntanx: {path:'',component:componentClassName}

            5. Dependency Injection - to share data between classes

            6. Angular Services - for reuse data

            7. ngSubmit - to submit entire form syntax: (ngSubmit)="funtion()"

            8. Angular Forms

                8.1 Template Driven Forms - First sign html

                8.2 Model Driven Forms - First create model in ts

                    8.2.1 Reactive Forms - Add Validation: Import ReactiveFormsModule                              11-luminar
                            -form group -  FormBuilder dependency inject , form array, form control, form control

            9 Angular Directives - To manipulate DOM

                9.1 Component Directives

                9.2 Structural Directives - To Change DOM structure

                    9.2.1 ngIf - syntax: *ngIf="condition"

                    9.2.2 ngFor - syntax: *ngFor="iterator of array-name" 

                9.3 Attribute Directives - to apply set of style to html

                    9.3.1 Predefined - eg: ngClass

                    9.3.2 Userdefined 

            10. Local Storage - to permanently store data in browser

                10.1 setItem()

                10.2 getItem()

                10.3 removeItem()
            
            11. Angular Pipes: to convert the data format
                    syntax: expression | pipe operator [ : pipe Arguments]

        
            12. Animation

            13. parent- child Communication 

                13.1 Parent to child : Input decorator

                13.2 Child to parent : Output decorator

            14. Event emitter - to generate userdefined events

                14.1 emit() - to occur the event

            15. Client - SErver Integration

                15.1 API - HttpClient

            16. Asynchronus Function resolving - RxJS

                16.1 Observable - resolved state - .subscribe
